Hydraulic Structures
Publisher: Taylor & Francis | 640 pages | July 2, 2001 | ISBN: 0415250706 | PDF 

Provides a comprehensive introduction to the strucyural aspects of hydraulics. The authors explain dam engineering, the design and construction of embankments, dam outlet works, hydroelectric power development and pumping stations. It also contains worked examples to help the reader comprehend the structural processes discussed. This brand new third edition contains new and expanded subject matter on strength and compressibility, air transport tunnels, dam-break analysis and coastal engineering.
